news.title: Housing societies in Kolkata scramble to tighten rent rules
news.para: Officiating members of some housing complexes have convened a meeting on Sunday to discuss the issue and strengthen renting rules, especially to foreigners.

news.title: No parking business at residential plot: Karnataka HC
news.para: Justice Suraj Govindaraj also observed that BBMP and traffic police cannot contend that they are unable to take action because a private area is used for parking vehicles.

news.title: Mapletree Investments buys 41 acre land in Bengaluru for Rs 1,900 crore
news.para: The transaction, valued at over Rs 1,900 crore, forms a key aspect of Adarsh Developers' strategy to alleviate debt burdens. With an estimated development potential of approximately 7 million square feet.

news.title: Daughter of Divi Laboratories' founder buys two Hyderabad properties for Rs 80 crore
news.para: Properties across significant markets such as Mumbai, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Delhi-NCR that only the super-rich can afford have seen huge demand in the last two years.

news.title: Defence Ministry objects to Godrej Properties' project in Mumbai
news.para: The Godrej Reserve project is being built on an 18.6-acre land parcel. The developer has already launched about 1.91 million sq ft and had got bookings for 1.51 million sq ft worth Rs 2,693 crore, according to the company's FY24 regulatory filing.

news.title: Date of house possession key for tax benefit: ITAT
news.para: This ruling is important, as for availing tax benefits, investment in a new house must be made within a specific period of time. To the extent of investment in the new house, the taxable component of long-term capital gains is reduced.

news.title: China Vanke granted $2.8 billion onshore syndicated loan facility
news.para: Lenders include a group of banks, led by state-owned Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC), which was in early talks to lend as much as 80 billion yuan, sources have said.

news.title: Brigade Group signs JDA to develop 6.9 acres land in Bengaluru
news.para: The project has a total development potential of around 0.8 million sq ft and gross development value of Rs 720 core.

news.title: Puravankara posts net loss of Rs 6.71 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Puravankara's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 946.84 crore, a growth of 116.97 per cent from Rs 436.39 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: German housing stagnates amidst wider property crisis in 2023
news.para: Around 294,400 apartments were built last year, 0.3% fewer than in 2022 and far below the government's target of building 400,000 apartments annually, Federal Statistics Office data showed on Thursday.

news.title: Truliv aims to achieve Rs 50-crore revenue in FY25
news.para: Truliv aims to add 3,500 more beds in FY24-25 and expand its presence further in the western and southern markets. "We aim to achieve Rs 50-crore topline in FY 2024–25," said co-founder and CEO of the company.

news.title: Existing home sales in USA fall 1.9% in April 2024
news.para: Though the report from the National Association of Realtors on Wednesday showed inventory increasing last month to a 2-1/2-year high entry-level homes remained scarce, accounting for the second straight monthly decline in sales.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit up 41.13% in Q4 FY24
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,807.15 crore in Q4 FY24, a dip of 3.81 per cent from Rs 1,878.76 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: YEIDA plans to offer 6,000 plots near Noida international airport
news.para: Noida International Airport and industrial clusters near the expressway are expected to boost the region's growth. The Yamuna Expressway Authority plans to launch an affordable residential scheme with small plots to accommodate low-income groups.

news.title: MahaRERA suspends registration of 20,000 real estate brokers
news.para: The registrations of an additional 20,000 agents have been suspended for one year for not obtaining MahaRERA's real estate agent certificate of competency or not uploading the certificate on the watchdog's website, an official statement said.

news.title: High-value homes drive residential market in Hyderabad
news.para: Hyderabad's residential property market in 2024 saw a 15% increase in property registrations and a 40% surge in transaction value, driven by demand for premium homes. Knight Frank's report revealed 26,027 properties registered, totaling Rs 16,190 crore.

news.title: Unsold real estate properties declines by 57% in Delhi-NCR: Report
news.para: The report added, the unsold real stock in the national capital region declined from approx. 2 lakh units at Q1 2018-end to approx. 86,420 units by Q1 2024-end.

news.title: Property registrations in Maharashtra hit amid tech glitch
news.para: The problem is primarily pertaining to the cloud services. Our teams are working on resolving the issues. The service is expected to be restored soon,” an official said.

news.title: Several cities in China slash down payments & mortgage rates to boost property demand
news.para: The down payment for first-time homebuyers in Hefei city and Wuhan city have been lowered from 20% to 15% - the lowest ratio allowed that the central bank announced last week, Shanghai Securities News reported on Wednesday.

news.title: L&T Realty inks pact for joint development of 12.2-acre land in Thane
news.para: The current developer Jagdale Infrastructure has received a letter of intent from the Slum Rehabilitation Authority in 2022 and is now bringing in L&T Realty as its partner in the project.
